{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "src/index.ts",
      "use": "@vercel/node"
    }
  ],
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/(.*)",
      "dest": "src/index.ts"
    }
  ]
}
```

**What changed:**
- `node/src/index.ts` → `src/index.ts` (removed the redundant `node/` prefix)
- `/api/(.*)` → `/(.*)` (catch ALL routes, not just `/api/` — your app handles its own routing internally)

---

## After saving, do this:

**1. Commit and push** the fixed `vercel.json`

**2. In Vercel dashboard** confirm settings:

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Root Directory | `backend/node` |
| Build Command | `npm run build` |
| Install Command | `npm install` |

**3. Redeploy**, then test these URLs:
```
https://your-vercel-url.vercel.app/health
https://your-vercel-url.vercel.app/api/node/health
